        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 2:28PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 228 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northwest of Gastonia, or near Dallas, moving northeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gastonia, Mt Holly, Bessemer City, Dallas, Stanley, Ranlo, High
Shoals, Iron Station, Lowell, and Lowesville.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
